<DOC><DOCNO> AP890503-0292 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-03-89 1911EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-FirstBoston-MetLife     05-03 0204</FIRST><SECOND>BC-First Boston-Met Life,0212</SECOND><HEAD>Met Life Buys 10 Percent of Investment Firm</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   CS First Boston Co. said Wednesday thatMetropolitan Life Insurance Co. has bought about 10 percent of theinvestment firm.   The value of the sale was not disclosed by the privately heldNew York-based investment firm. It said the shares being sold arepart of a 30.5 percent holding of Saudi Arabian investor SulimanOlayan.   CS First Boston was formed in a $1.1 billion merger of FirstBoston Inc. and Financiere Credit Suisse-First Boston of London.   ``The transaction is a strategic investment which we expect willsubstantially extend our global reach as part of our long-rangeplan to develop a worldwide business and investment capability,''Met Life Chairman Robert G. Schwartz said in a statement.   The Swiss banking conglomerate Credit Suisse owns 44.5 percentof the new entity, giving it effective control and the largestforeign stake in a major Wall Street securities house. Managementpartners of First Boston own 25 percent.   First Boston and Credit Suisse created Financiere CreditSuisse-First Boston as a joint venture, in 1978.   Met Life, one of the nation's largest insurance and financialservices companies, manages more than $120 billion in assets.</TEXT></DOC>